rComments: Professor Restuccia is very knowledgeable about all things economics. While his lectures are not always very interesting (they are basically repeats of the textbook) if you go after class and ask him questions he will always give you a very well thought out response, no matter the relevance of the subject. I would recommend the class on that alone.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Very knowledgeable and relates course material to theoretical debates and empirical data. You need to practice within time limits to do well on his tests: speed is of the essence.

Pros: Knows what he is teaching and can clear all your doubts Cons: Gives lesser than necessary time to complete the paper. Speaks monotonously. Does not have office hours, although he answers all questions after class.
Just take his Eco362 class. You will love it
excellent instructor, he should be an example to other professors in the economics department (especially you, Loren Brandt)
One of the nicest people I've ever met on campus. Really friendly and udnerstanding. His tests and exams are hard though, and I thought they were marked really hard...
One of the nicest people I've met in university. He teaches well and treats students with utmost respect. Too bad his tests and exams are hard. The marking scheme for the course is also really harsh.
